column25: Arabidopsis thaliana WT pollen grain control
column27: Arabidopsis thaliana WT and mutant cngc16 pollen grain heat stress transcriptome
column29: Transcriptomes were analyzed from mature pollen grains harvested at midday from plants grown under normal (control) conditions to compare to pollen from plants with a heat stress regime. For the stress condition, plants were grown under a diurnal cycle of hot and cold temperatures and pollen were harvested at the end of a HS period that peaked at 40 degrees Celsius.
